@saksarav-nokia There is sonic mgmt infrastructure that expects to be able to control the appropriate asics by prepending the network namespace.

https://github.com/sonic-net/sonic-mgmt/blob/98d24345964a12ec7c9174bc0687afc802630e74/tests/common/devices/sonic_asic.py#L38

The utilities CLIs are expected to work in this fashion

I had a few reasons why I wanted to use this method including backwards compatibility, following the principal of least astonishment, usage with the SonicAsic class. This change seemed like a good way to extend the functionality and make the test pass at the same time.

But if the expectation is that all utilities commands are migrating from the network namespace to the -n flag then I will make the change in MGMT instead

